        <div class="billbox">
            <div class="billhead">
<pre>
_   /|
\'o.O'
=(___)=
   U    ack!
</pre>
            </div>
            <div class="billtext">
                <h1>ack is a tool like grep, optimized for programmers</h1>

                <p>
                Designed for programmers with large heterogeneous
                trees of source code, ack is written purely in
                portable Perl and takes advantage of the power of
                Perl's regular expressions.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-bullets">
            <dl>
                <dt>Blazing Fast</dt>
                <dd>It's fast because it only searches the stuff it makes sense to search.</dd>

                <dt>Runs on Windows</dt>
                <dd>ack is pure Perl, so it runs on a Windows Perl
                (like <a href="http://strawberryperl.com/">Strawberry Perl</a>) without modifications.</dd>

                <dt>Better Search</dt>
                <dd>Searches entire trees by default while ignore Subversion, Git and other VCS directories
                and other files that aren't your source code.</dd>

                <dt>Fewer Keystrokes</dt>
                <dd>ack uses fewer keystrokes for common tasks than grep</dd>

                <dt>Free and open</dt>
                <dd>Ack costs nothing.  It's 100% free and open source.</dd>
            </dl>
        </div>
        [% PROCESS 'google.tt' %]
    </body>
